This paper deals with measuring the similarity of ranked lists, which is a topic related to data mining (cs.DM) and machine learning (cs.LG). The paper also involves the use of mathematical inequalities, which falls under information theory (cs.IT). Additionally, the paper may be relevant to social networks (cs.SI) and computational complexity (cs.CC) as these fields often involve analyzing and comparing large sets of data.
